    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with a high-upside core anchored by **Trevor Story** (73.82) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.49). **Trevor Story** profiles as our premier play; while Spencer Arrighetti is a serviceable arm, the 4.76 xERA and a slow delivery to the plate create an elite environment for **Trevor Story** to exploit both his power stroke and our priority on stolen bases. Similarly, **Tyler Soderstrom** draws a highly favorable matchup against Slade Cecconi. With a significant park boost and a platoon advantage that pushes his efficiency score well into the strong category, **Tyler Soderstrom** is primed for a multi-hit performance that bolsters our counting stats. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (70.89) rounds out the top tier, benefiting from a robust platoon edge against Emerson Hancock that should yield high-leverage RBI opportunities.\n\nStrategic maneuvering at the bottom of the lineup necessitates careful monitoring of the \"Lineup Pending\" status for catchers **Dalton Rushing** and **Luis Campusano**. While **Dalton Rushing** (55.22) sits safely above our floor, **Luis Campusano** (45.72) is hanging on primarily due to slot necessity; his value is suppressed by a projected #9 hole and a neutral platoon matchup against Sean Burke. The most difficult personnel decision today involved **Travis Bazzana** (46.50), who narrowly missed the starting cut. Despite an elite xwOBA of .408, his negative platoon split against Jacob Lopez and the lack of a locked-in batting order forced the optimizer to prefer the higher-floor profiles of our starting outfielders. We are also proceeding with caution regarding **Mickey Moniak** (47.39); while he benefits from a park-factor surge, the daunting matchup against Chris Sale creates a significant volatility risk that could render him a liability if he fails to capitalize on early-game opportunities.",
